title: A look at Saturday Night Live's most memorable characters
text: Blogs A look at Saturday Night Live's most memorable characters In 1975, Lorne Michaels created a little variety television show that was broadcast live, originally titled "NBC's Saturday Night." Fast forward 40 years, and you have yourself "Saturday Night Live" so why not take a look back at 40 of the most iconic characters and memorable sketches. Photo: NBC via Getty Images./ Published: 10/11/2015 11:29:24 'Wayne's World' Shwing! Wayne Campbell and Garth Algar, played by Mike Myers (l.) and Dana Carvey (r.) in the sketch "WayneÂ’s World," a television show broadcasted from Wayne's parents' basement that discussed babes, music and had special guests that they'd trick into saying vulgar words.
